Steps to run the code:

1.	First download all the libraries in the system mentioned in the notebook file (yelp_test.ipynb). 
2.	You can have any environment such as jupyter notebook or VS code to run the code.
3.	Next put the dataset (yelp.csv) in the same folder as the script file.
4.	Run each part of the notebook and run all the parts until the testing is done.
5.	Next, open yelp_api.py and run the script after downloading all the necessary libraries.
6.	The terminal will suggest a url which you need to copy paste on browser.
7.	Then enter any text for the final output.
